<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193114>
    bibo:endPage "39" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "21" ;
    bibo:volume "2332" ;
    dc:creator "Rodriguez, Pilar; Achurra, Ainara" ;
    dc:date "2010" ;
    dc:title "New species of aquatic oligochaetes (Annelida: Clitellata) from groundwaters in karstic areas of northern Spain, with taxonomic remarks on Lophochaeta ignota Štolc, 1886" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193115>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193116>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193117>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193118>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193119> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193115>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Gianius navarroi n. sp. A: general diagram of the reproductive organs of the species, X and XI: segment number; B: free-hand drawing of somatic chaeta. Abbreviations: a: atrium, mp: male pore, o: ovary, pc: penial chaetae, pgI and pgII: prostate glands I and II, sf: sperm funnel, sa: spermathecal ampulla, sd: spemathecal duct, ss: sperm sacs, t: testis, vd: vas deferens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193115/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193116>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Isochaetides gianii n. sp. Somatic chaetae (A – D: free-hand drawings at the same scale). A: anterior ventral; B: posterior ventral; C: anterior pectinate dorsal; D: posterior dorsal; E: anterior bundle of pectinate and hair chaetae; F: spermathecal chaeta. Scale bars: E and F: 25 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193116/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193117>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Isochaetides gianii n. sp. A: commissural blood vessels in body segments V and VI; B: anterior end of the body, arrow pointing to the glands on the pharynx, in segment III; C: sudden transition to the intestine, from segments VII to VIII; D: spermatheca; E: detail of spermatheca in a histological section; F: penial sac with penis; G: cross histological section of penial sac; H: longitudinal histological section of penial sac. Abbreviations: ag: accessory gland, cps: cuticular penial sheath, i: intestine, p: penis, rf: ring fold of the penial sac, sa: spermathecal ampulla, sch: spermathecal chaeta, sd: spermathecal duct, sz: spermatozeugmata, vf: ventral fold of the spermatheca. Scale bars: A – D 100 µm, E – H: 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193117/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193118>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Isochaetides gianii n. sp. General diagram of the reproductive organs. X and XI: segment number. Abbreviations: a: atrium, ag: accessory gland, cps: cuticular penial sheath, o: ovary, pg: prostate gland, ps: penial sac, sa: spermathecal ampulla, sch: spermathecal chaeta, sd: spermathecal duct, sg: chaetal gland, t: testis, vd: vas deferens, vf: ventral fold of the body wall." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193118/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.193119>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Isochaetides freyi (Brinkhurst, 1965). A: histological section of the atrium; B: penial sac with penis lined by cuticle; C: ventral fold of the body wall, where the spermathecal duct opens; D: spermatheca. Abbreviation s: a: atrium, c: chaetophore, cps: cuticular penial sheath, p: penis, pg: prostate gland, sa: spermathecal ampulla, sch: spermathecal chaeta, sd: spermathecal duct, vd: vas deferens, vf: ventral fold of the body wall. Scale bars: 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/193119/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

